        <mxCell id="p6b" parent="1" style="text;html=0;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacingLeft=4;spacingTop=4;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Before authorizing any failure class for autonomous execution, answer two questions: &#xa;&#xa;How far does blast radius reach if the fix is wrong? &#xa;What is the rollback path? &#xa;&#xa;Not just: how likely is the fix to be right. &#xa;The asymmetry is real, and the staged autonomy model exists precisely because of it." vertex="1">
